Impact of Covid-19 on Air Traffic in Europe

Stephen Sani

2024-04-08

Introduction

Covid-19 is probably the most important single event in the year 2019. As the virus spread across the globe, governments around the world began to take measures to curb the transmission of the virus. One such measures was restrictions on air travels in addition, some imposed a total loackdown of part orentire country. The measures taken seem to immediately affected air travel and it is widely believed that covid-19 have affected most aspects of human lives. In this report, we will investigate the impact of covid-19 and associated restrictions on air traffic. The data source is from Eurocontrol. Eurocontrol minitors air traffic in airports across Europe. For example, we are interestes in 1. the trend of total traffic by year 2. the trend of difference between arrival and departure 3. The effect on top ten airports with highest traffic in 2019 and 2020.

Let us preview records with missing values

All missing values are from airport operator. Missing values not entered by airport operator are already captured by network manager. we will use entries from network manager. Let us drop all entries from airport operator as most of them are missing.

Conclussion

Covid-19 and the associated measures taken by governments around the word to control its spread have led to a decrease in air traffic in European states. In addition, the difference in the number of arrival and number of departure have increased in the years following covid-19 in comparison to the years before covid-19. Finally, while all airports have been impacted, most of the top ten airports with the highest traffic before covid-19 continue to be among the top ten performers even after covid-19.
